Points are awarded for the following actions :

Moving a card from the deck to the tableau ................. 35 Points
Moving a card from the deck/tableau to the foundations ..... 80 Points
Moving a card from The Demon to the Tableau ............... 140 Points
Moving a card from The Demon to the foundations ........... 200 Points

Every second of elapsed time ............................... -1 Point
Each use of the Undo function ............................. -50 Points
Each use of the Find Foundations option ................... -50 Points


If the game is completed, a bonus is awarded based on the time taken :

              350 seconds and over ........... 2000 Points
              300 to 349 seconds ............. 2500 Points
              250 to 299 seconds ............. 3000 Points
              200 to 249 seconds ............. 3500 Points
              175 to 199 seconds ............. 4000 Points
              150 to 174 seconds ............. 4500 Points
              Under 150 seconds .............. 5000 Points

If you use either game rule 2 or 4, where you can only move complete
columns, then the bonus will be increased by 100 Points.

If you start the game with a thirteen card Demon, the maximum
possible score will be as follows :

Thirteen Demon cards to the tableau ........... 13 x 140 = 1820
Thirty four deck cards to the tableau ......... 34 x 35  = 1190
Fifty one tableau cards to the foundations .... 51 x 80  = 4080
Achieving this in under 150 seconds ........... Bonus    = 5100
                                                         ------
                                Maximum Possible Score = 12,190
                                                         ------

When playing with a ten card Demon, the maximum score is 11,875

These scores will be further reduced by up to 149 points depending on
the exact time taken to complete the game.

Scores of 10,000+ are ones to be proud of.

